data.enText: a person whose job is to take care of sheep
to guide sb or a group of people somewhere, making sure they go where you want them to go

tr: a herder of sheep (on an open range)
someone who keeps the sheep together in a flock
a clergyman who watches over a group of people
tend as a shepherd, as of sheep or goats
watch over like a shepherd, as a teacher of her pupils

value.def: A shepherd is a person, especially a man, whose job is to look after sheep.
If you are shepherded somewhere, someone takes you there to make sure that you arrive at the right place safely.

example.ex: She was shepherded by her guards up the rear ramp of the aircraft.
example.tran: 她在警卫的护送下上了飞机尾部的舷梯。
